## Monorepo map (high level)

- `apps/web`: Next.js 16 + React 19 + Tailwind CSS (utility-first). Prefer Radix UI + shadcn-style patterns already present.
- `apps/api`: Hono API on Node (TypeScript, ESM). OpenAPI via `@hono/zod-openapi`.
- `packages/database`: Prisma + Supabase client utilities, TypeScript build output in `dist/`.
- `packages/types`: Shared TypeScript types (compiled via `tsc`).
- `packages/eslint-config`: Shared ESLint config packages.
- `packages/typescript-config`: Shared TS config package.

## Rule precedence

- When editing files under a subproject, treat the nearest nested rules in that subproject (e.g. `apps/web/.cursor/rules/*`) as higher priority than this global file.
- If global guidance conflicts with a subproject’s guidance, follow the subproject.

## Repo-wide conventions

- Use `pnpm` (repo pins `pnpm@9.0.0`) and Turbo (`turbo run ...`) for scripts.
- Node engine is `22.x`.
- Keep changes scoped: don’t refactor unrelated code, don’t “format the whole repo”.
- Prefer existing patterns in the repo over introducing new frameworks/libraries.

## TurboRepo workflow & caching

- Prefer `turbo run <task>` over ad-hoc workspace commands so caching stays effective.
- When adding or changing Turbo tasks (`turbo.json`), ensure:
  - Tasks declare correct `dependsOn` relationships (including upstream `^build` style dependencies where appropriate).
  - Tasks declare correct `outputs` so caching is safe (don’t cache the world; don’t forget build artifacts).
  - Environment variables are handled deliberately:
    - Avoid leaking secrets via overly-broad “global” env configuration.
    - Prefer validating required env vars per app/package at runtime boundaries.
- If a change affects build outputs (e.g. Next build, Prisma generate, TypeScript build), ensure the relevant task produces output into the expected directory (`.next/`, `dist/`, etc.).

## TypeScript

- Keep strict typing. Avoid `any` unless there is a clear boundary (e.g. third-party payload) and you immediately validate/narrow.
- Prefer `zod` schemas where input validation is needed.

